tta_section][vc_tta_section title="Perform value engineering" tab_id="1491214487146-8c8ca904-f91a"][vc_column_text]The reasoning behind value engineering is as follows: if marketers expect a product to become practically or stylistically obsolete within a specific length of time, they can design it to only last for that specific lifetime.[/vc_column_text][/vc_tta_section][vc_tta_section title="INSPECTIONS AND OCCUPANCY PERMIT" tab_id="1491214486434-e8868305-e7a1"][vc_column_text]The products could be built with higher-grade components, but with value engineering they are not because this would impose an unnecessary cost on the manufacturer, and to a limited extent also an increased cost on the purchaser. Value engineering will reduce these costs. A company will typically use the least expensive components that satisfy the product\'s lifetime projections.[/vc_column_text][/vc_tta_section][/vc_tta_accordion][/vc_column][/vc_row]', 'meta' => array ( '_vc_post_settings' => array ( 0 => 'a:1:{s:10:"vc_grid_id";a:0:{}}', ), '_edit_lock' => array ( 0 => '1510209442:1', ), '_edit_last' => array ( 0 => '1', ), 'slide_template' => array ( 0 => 'default', ), '_wpb_vc_js_status' => array ( 0 => 'true', ), '_thumbnail_id' => array ( 0 => '1266', ), 'page_title_box' => array ( 0 => 'true', ), 'page_title_box_align' => array ( 0 => 'left', ), 'page_title_breadcrumbs' => array ( 0 => 'true', ), 'page_title_box_line_color' => array ( 0 => 'ffffff', ), 'prev_next' => array ( 0 => 'true', ), 'page_title_prev_next' => array ( 0 => 'true', ), 'gallery' => array ( 0 => 'a:6:{i:0;i:1271;i:1;i:1269;i:2;i:1268;i:3;i:1267;i:4;i:1266;i:5;i:1267;}', ), 'client' => array ( 0 => 'Awesome Company, ABC Group', ), 'location' => array ( 0 => 'Mountain View CA 94043', ), 'surface' => array ( 0 => '450,000 m2', ), 'completed' => array ( 0 => 'September, 2015', ), 'value' => array ( 0 => '$15 250 000', ), 'architect' => array ( 0 => 'Pei Cobb Freed & Partners', ), '_wp_old_slug' => array ( 0 => 'golden